The paper focuses on analyzing the temporal and social properties of apps in a social ecosystem, which involves aspects of social networks, user behavior, and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
